It would be helpful for a supervisor or administrator to be able to log work for someone else.  Right now, you can only log work for yourself.

This should probably be configured as a separate permission, so that only certain people could log work for others.

This is related to JRA-1669.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-1649].
  {panel}

Sometimes I need to close JIRA down due to maintenance.

Right now I do this by only allowing JIRA administrators to login. This has the bad side effect that anybody else are told that "Sorry, your username and password are incorrect - please try again.". Then they try to require a new password (and do this about 3 times before they contact me).

If they instead got the message "Sorry, you are not able to login at the moment due to system maintenance" it would be much better.

