When we create an issue we also create an internal bug test case with the same issue name. So, many times, we'll have an issue description like:

"Blah blah blah doesn't work. See SMA-102.cs and SMA-102.xml for bug reproduction."

JIRA seems to automatically hotlink the SMA-102 to the actual issue inside JIRA. This is really cool, actually, but it would be nice if it were smart enough to look for more text and not link if it existed. So, putting SMA-102 by itself, surrounded by spaces, would be cause a hot link, but putting SMA-102anythingelsehere would not.

